@subsubsection Multiline Edit

A multi line edit controls type is ``Multiline Edit''.

@subsubheading Signals

Multi line edit controls send the following signals.

@table @code
@item signalPaste
Generated when the clipboard has been pasted.

@item signalCopy
Generated when the marked area has been copied into the clipboard.

@item signalCut
Generated when the marked area has been cut into the clipboard.

@item signalEnter
Generated when the event occured the appends/inserts a new line (usually the Enter key).

@item signalRowChanged
Generated when the cursor enters a new row.

@item signalColChanged
Generated when the cursor enters a new column.

@item signalLostFocus
Generated when the component has lost it's input focus.

@end table

@subsubheading Attributes

Textboxes publish the following attributes.

@table @code
@item Style
The following styles manipulate the appearance of the components frame:
@itemize
@item mefsBump
@item mefsSimple
@item mefsRaised
@item mefsSunken
@item mefsFlat
@item mefsNone
@end itemize
These styles define what background is used.
@itemize
@item meNormal:
The skins @samp{Texture} is used to draw the background.
@item meBitmap:
The texture defined in attribute @samp{Bitmap} is used to draw the background.
@end itemize

@item Alpha
The alpha of the applied background textures.

@item CursorColor
This triplet defines the color of the cursor. If not given the skins @samp{TextForeColor} is used.

@item Font
A font name. This font is used to draw the content of this control. It is tried to load it from the systems fontserver.
If it fails the default font of @sc{aws} is used.

@item Bitmap
If the style is @samp{fsBitmap} then this attribute is used to define the image used as the controls background image.

@end table

@subsubheading Skin Attributes

Multiline edit controls support the following skin attributes.

@table @code
@item Texture
Texture used to draw the components background

@item ButtonTextureAlpha
The default alpha value used when drawing the background texture.

@item TextForeColor
The default color used to draw the cursor.

@end table

@subsubheading Properties

Multiline edit controls publish the following properties.

@table @code
@item Font
A font name for a font to use when drawing text. This property is write-only.

@item iFont
A pointer to an iFont to use when drawing text. This property is write-only.

@end table

@subsubheading Actions

Multiline edit controls understand the following actions.

@itemize
@item @ref{mledInsertRow,,InsertRow}
@item @ref{mledDeleteRow,,DeleteRow}
@item @ref{mledReplaceRow,,ReplaceRow}
@item @ref{mledGetRow,,GetRow}
@item @ref{mledGetRowCount,,GetRowCount}
@item @ref{mledGetText,,GetText}
@item @ref{mledSetText,,SetText}
@item @ref{mledClear,,Clear}
@end itemize

@anchor{mledInsertRow}
@table @code
@item @strong{InsertRow}
Inserts a new string at a specified row position.
@end table

@subsubheading Input Parameters

@multitable @columnfractions .15 .2 .55
@item @emph{Name}
@tab @emph{Type}
@tab @emph{Description}

@item @code{row}
@tab @code{int}
@tab The row number the new string should become.

@item @code{string}
@tab @code{iString*}
@tab The actual string that will be displayed in the new row.

@end multitable

@subsubheading Output Parameters

None.

@anchor{mledDeleteRow}
@table @code
@item @strong{DeleteRow}
Deletes the row at a specified row position.
@end table

@subsubheading Input Parameters

@multitable @columnfractions .15 .2 .55
@item @emph{Name}
@tab @emph{Type}
@tab @emph{Description}

@item @code{row}
@tab @code{int}
@tab The row to delete.

@end multitable

@subsubheading Output Parameters

None.

